The paper presents an algorithm for sparsifying weighted graphs, which involves data structures and algorithms for computing effective resistances. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.CG (computational geometry), cs.NA (numerical analysis), cs.SI (social and information networks), and cs.IT (information theory). Among these, cs.DS and cs.CG are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on algorithmic techniques for graph sparsification and effective resistance computation. The other categories are also possible, as the paper discusses applications of sparsification to network analysis and optimization.
